To calculate the binomial coefficient (also known as "n choose k") in Ada, you can use the `factorial` function along with some arithmetic operations. The formula for calculating a binomial coefficient is: C(n, k) = n! / [k!(n-k)!].

Here's an example of how to implement it in Ada:

```ada
with Ada.Text_IO; use Ada.Text_IO;
with Ada.Numerics.Discrete_Math;

procedure Binomial_Coefficient is
   type Integer is range 0 .. 100; -- You can adjust the range as needed
   function Factorial ( N : Integer ) return Natural is
      result : Natural := 1;
   begin
      for I in 2 .. N loop
         result := result * I;
      end loop;
      return result;
   end Factorial;

   function Binomial_Coefficient ( N : Integer; K : Integer ) return Natural is
      C : Natural;
   begin
      if K > N then
         Put_Line ("Error: K must be less than or equal to N.");
         exit;
      end if;

      C := Factorial(N) / (Factorial(K) * Factorial(N - K));
      return C;
   end Binomial_Coefficient;
begin
   Put ("Enter the value of N: ");
   N : Integer;
   Get (N);
   Put ("Enter the value of K: ");
   K : Integer;
   Get (K);
   Put_Line ("The binomial coefficient C(N, K) is: " & Natural'Image (Binomial_Coefficient (N, K)));
end Binomial_Coefficient;
```

